# kopah-bagit configuration
#
# Pick ONE of the two auth options below. If both are set, S3CMD_CONFIG wins.
# Failing to set either causes kopah-bagit to exit non-zero with a clear error.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A (recommended for operators who already run s3cmd against Kopah):
# Point at the s3cmd INI file. kopah-bagit reads access_key, secret_key, and
# host_base from its [default] section. Same pattern as storage-scripts.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# S3CMD_CONFIG=/Users/you/.s3cfg-kopah

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B (direct env vars, useful for CI / containers):
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KOPAH_ACCESS_KEY=...
# KOPAH_SECRET_KEY=...
# KOPAH_ENDPOINT=https://s3.kopah.uw.edu
